,Recommended,245170,19052317,"Posted: 13 November, 2015",all,Vito,"This is a review, that you should take to heart and shall help you to either decide to buy the game or not.Ilovethis game, if you couldn't tell. I play this game on a daily basis for 2 up to 5 hours a day and I will not get sick of it. I enjoy every second of it. From the music and stages, characters and their stories, up to the developers and voiceactors themselves; I just say, that I fell in love with this game. Of course, there are some flaws in this game, that I want to say in this review, so please, if you are not sure if this game is for you, then I hope, that I'll be able to help you.The Game:The game itself is basically what you get, when you throw Street Fighter, Mortal Kombat and your favorite anime waifu in a pot and mix it all together. It's a 2D Fighting Game with it's own certain mechanics and finally; Smooth 60 FPS. It is usually played with a Fighting/Arcade Stick, (Depends of how you call it) but on steam, you can play it with the Keyboard, XBox or Playstation controller... The choices are yours and yours only. If you prefer the Keyboard over the controller, go ahead.The CharactersThe Game has a selection of 14 characters, everyone of them with their own unique playstyle. As the title says, there are mostly only female characters. I repeat;mostly.With the exception of two characters, who are male, (Three, if you count Robo-Fortune as genderless) the rest of them are all female, but that does not matter. They all also have their own individual stories, which I like to tell you now.The Story/StoriesThe Story goes like this;A mystic artifact known as the Skullheart has been created since multiple decades. It's power was to grant any girl's wish, if they were pure in the heart, but most of them weren't. If they were not, they turned into a creature, called the ""Skullgirl"", who brought chaos, death and armageddon to a teaparty to wreck her surroundings. If the Skullheart got destroyed however, it will come back 7 years later to find a new victim and the cycle goes on and on and on... Until year HellIfIKnow, where the new Skullgirls ""Bloody Marie"" has risen and brings havoc to New Meridian.The character's stories are fixed and cannot be changed, whether you like it or not. Why am I telling you this? The stories of many characters end dramatically, sometimes death is included, which can be hard hitting for you, if you have a strong bound to your favorite character.I'm sorry, Squigly :cI will not tell how their story goes onward from that point, you will either have to watch a walkthrough on youtube or play the game by yourself.GameplayNow, the gameplay is depending of what you play with. For me; I currently play with the keyboard and I improved with time. It however is definitely best played with the Fighting/Arcade Stick, so if you have one, you probably have it easy.MultiplayerThis is where you have to admit; Multiplayer in this game sucksONLYif you play with people, that you don't know. Joining a random lobby in Skullgirls will be the bane of your life, eventually making you stop playing the game even. Believe me, when I say this; You will not like the random lobbies in Skullgirls. You will get literally ♥♥♥♥ed over and over, if you started playing the game. It is recommended to get a few friends to play this game and you probably get better in it.I still stuck at it tho.My Judgement of ""Skullgirls""This game is considered in my eyes a great game, that I refuse to actually let go from. I am a Skullgirls-Addict with 150 Hours, but the hours will rise higher and higher the more often I boot it up. It is funny, you get in the mood to play it more and more, you want to learn to become better in it until you want to become the best in Skullgirls.Skullgirls gets a 8 out of 10TL;DR: Good Game, stay away from multiplayer, if you have no friends.Thanks to To LabZeroGames for Skullgirls and MikeZ for keeping the community uplightenedand for that awesome Soviet Announcer <3"
