,Not Recommended,245170,7669795,"Posted: 16 November, 2013",all,Serphius,"I can't recommend this game except to people who have spent comprehensive time with fighting games. I wanted to like it, but ultimately regret the purchase.The art style and animation is a strong point, and the characters are enjoyable if you don't mind heavy fanservice. But, the actual gameplay is pretty terrible towards newer players. The tutorials establish fighting game rules pretty well, but they really don't help when playing against other actual people. The matchmaking prioritizes internet connection over skill/ranking, leading to a ton of matches where you will literally put down your controller while someone lands a 50-hit combo on you.This leads to a game that is extremely off-putting to casual players, as it doesnt allow you to gradually improve by playing others of your own skill level. Learning the basics through the fantastic tutorials will not help when getting regularly matched against veterans that only need to land one hit to win the match.Perhaps it's better if you stick with a small group of friends. But, with the emphasis on overly-long combos and inability to consistently play strangers of your own skill level, I would recommend SSFIV or KOF over this fighter for casual players. Only buy if it's on a really good sale or you are otherwise accustomed to combo-based fighting systems. It's really a game for veterans, which unfortunately I was not."
