,Recommended,245170,28872687,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,President Trump,"Honestly, the game's characters looked very weird to me at first. That took me aback for a long time, until I decided to give this game a shot. And well, what can I say, it's really good.The game looks great, the characters are very well animated and most importantly, playing it is really fun.You can choose characters and group them in teams of 2, 3 or go solo. The smaller the team, the stronger each individual character is in terms of stats. You can combine the teams and choose the assist attack for the other teammates to get some really flashy and neat combos.One thing this game does right is having a pretty extensive tutorial that teaches you about the game mechanics and the different characters, that will help beginners get a taste of what the game feels like, but without excluding more experienced fighter players, since the game is complex enough and characters are more or less balanced in that there are no incredibly bad characters that are impossible to do win with.Not to mention an extensive training mode that includes information about hitboxes and the like.If you are a fan of fighting games, this might provide you with hours of fun. Beware though, there are lots of very good players wandering in online matches, so you will get your♥♥♥♥♥kicked at the beginning."
