,Recommended,245170,30984590,Posted: 6 April,all,jujubemaster,"+This game has great netcode(GGPO) which pretty much separates it from a decent amount of other fighters that don't use rollback based netcode(or don't even have online period).+Great art and voice work+Good tutorial which teaches some advanced techniques and helps players that are starting out.+Entourage feature. Pretty much allows you to load a team so you don't have to waste time picking out one. You can save a team by pressing an assist macro or by holding up or down along with an assist macro.=Team based fighter. You can use just one really strong character instead of a team if you want, but this game was designed around team play. If you want a 1v1 game, then this game can somewhat answer thatThe highly detailed art and assist usage can be confusing, especially to newer players. This game is also combo and reset heavy, but the combos are not very hard compared to other fighting games, just somewhat long. You do not have to rely on 1-2 frame links to do your bnbs. For people that really like tight links, there are some difficult combo routes and complicated resets."
