76561198103689957,Recommended,245170,9032472,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,Useful Idiot,"I wasn't expecting much from Skullgirls when I bought it, but it more then exceeded my expectations after playing the game for more then just an hour. This is a six button fighter that can be played with normal powered teams, a strong tag team, or an overpowered single character. The option to be able to choose how many chatacters you want to bring into a match allows you to play the game in a numerous of ways, and brings different learning curves.The in-game tutorial is the best I have seen in a fighting game, to date. This is a good place to start with fighters, just for the simple fact that it tries to teach newcomers the nuances of the genre, and not just combos. Although, there are plenty of advanced combos that require precise execution and memory, that put games like MvC and Blaz Blue to shame, if you are interested in high-level play.Controls are fluid and responsive, any time my fighter did something I didn't intend for her to do, I knew I was at fault and that it wasn't due to bad mechanics. Combos are easily to learn and execute but like all fighters, require some time to learn. I have tried playing with a Keyboard, Gamepad, and Arcade stick, and can say you will probably need a pad or stick to play this game. Don't get me wrong it is very possible to play with a keyboard, (and from personal experience, actually kinda fun) but it will be hard to play characters who rely on Z motions.The 2-D sprites are detailed and animated fluidly. The developers did a good job incorporating each characters personality into their fighting styles, if you can appreciate such things. Each character even has their own animation and properties for their tag ins and outs. (something I wish Marvel had)Even though most people probably don't go into fighters looking for a story, the game does feature a story mode, that has suprisingly good lore, and interesting characters, with a final boss that may well rival Shao Kahn. So even if you are looking for a single player fighter, there is something to be found here."
