,Recommended,245170,14443271,"Posted: 12 February, 2015",all,Fenix,"This game is actually pretty good.Besides that there's an obvious amount of fanservice, this game does have a lot to offer. The soundtrack is amazing, the story is quite good, and voice acting, taunting, animations in general, the anime-like graphics are all 10/10.The tutorial is good, teaches many different moves (until 1 moment i got stuck on it, but no problem). The community is made of many tryhard players, so there are really good guides on steam and on Skullgirls forum for each character and their different combos. It also has a infinity (combo) breaker system.Pick your characters (1-3 per game) and go fight. There are good interactions between the characters and also assists and assist combos. It's really good to play with friends, but also good to play online, the netcode (GGPO) is impressive, good enough so you don't feel delay or any lag while playing with people from different and far (!) locations. Usually when playing with friends the ping varied from 40-100 ms, but I've played on 350 ms and was still a smooth gameplay. Also you can always choose the location and skill level of people you want to play against. There is also a ranking system that accounts victories and losses, but I'm not sure how it works.I play this game on a keyboard and it's not bad at all. I don't have a controller but the game has a full controller support as well and I may try it one day.It's an easy to learn, but hard to master kind of game.I have fun with it even though I'm a noob.(y)"
