,Recommended,245170,32940554,Posted: 28 June,all,MadameLucario,"Arcade Beat-em-Ups, a genre that I hold dearly and close to my heart. The character assortment is pretty nice and the controls are quite smooth, especially if you own a controller that is compatible with your PC (of if you go the extra mile to get yourself a Steam Link and Steam Controller combo). However I am only scratching the surface of what this game has to offer.The story mode for this game is relative short given that you only fight in a set number of stages for each character, with each providing a piece of the story and various view points on how the main villain of the game (the Skull Heart) had devastated or affected the lives of many. It helps you know the character's set personalities and you never get bored with it. However, I will say that the final boss that you have to face each time is just a pain for me. The amount of times that I have died to the final boss is uite sad really, but that's mostly because of my poor reflexes. Doesn't stop me from having fun, though.The art style for these characters are absolutely beautiful and smooth. It gives me those traditionally drawn cartoon nostalgic vibes every time I see them and the camos that have been placed in the game don't fail to make me laugh either.I definitely recommend this to players who have always enjoyed playing fighting games such as Tekken and Street Fighter. It is definitely worth the money and it is even more engaging when you have friends playing against you. You have the choice of playing locally or online. I've played it a ton with my friends and hilarity certainly ensues when at least of of the people you're playing with only knows how to button mash.This game was certainly made for those who in general really enjoy video games and it does not matter your skill level in fight games, you are still guaranteed to at least have some fun."
