,Recommended,245170,33252021,Posted: 4 July,all,Aquariatus,"This is the first fighter I've ever played and honestly, I'm excited to try more.  The tutorials make for a really easy introduction that thoroughly explains what the heck is going on, and the adjustable CPU difficulties makes it easy to scale as you (hopefully) get better.  The wide variety of characters with different play styles makes it fun to try them all, and the many, many different modes allows for endless fun.  Some of the combos can be difficult to perfect but once you do it is SO satisfying. The controls are a little awkward, as are some of the combo inputs (I still can't do the Z pattern), but it's not super detrimental to game play (just play Fukua like me). Whether you're just randomly mashing buttons, or carefully executing movesets-- Skullgirls is truly wonderful for beginners and advanced players alike."
