,Recommended,245170,10846235,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,Rukinom,"As a gamer who was turned off to fighting games his whole life, Skullgirls really took me in.The tutorial is fantastic, covering everything from the basics of 2D fighting gameplay, to advanced techniques as specific as mixups and an entire lesson based on in-air cancels. It also has a lesson for each playable character, covering all their special attacks, proper strategy, and some sample combos.The art is stunning, the backgrounds and the characters all of have creative and clear designs. It visibly shows when an attack is blocked, so you aren't left guessing if a hit was confirmed. There are no cliche characters, and they all have very different fighting styles.Teams vs Solo is well balanced, allowing you team assists vs more health and damage. Almost all team setups work well together, and there's always a way to fill in a character's gaps with assists.The game plays like a AAA title, controls are tight and understandable, the design is fantastic, and it's a great intro to fighting games. Highly recommended."
