,Recommended,245170,2643520,"Posted: 25 August, 2013",all,q3.railgun,"A game designed by MikeZ, so right off the bat you'll know you're going into a combo heavy game. Interesting character designs and the game takes from a lot of different (but same combo heavy type) fighters.The game was originally started based off of MvC2 so that's where most of the tag team aspect comes in. The matches can be anything from (1-3)v(1-3) (CvS2 ratios). If you have more than 2 players you get to choose your assist (mvc2 style) but you can also use a custom assist which can be as simple as a lp or as advanced as a different move which is not originally selectable. DHC's are in this game so if you whiff a super you can DHC to another character which has a safer on-miss option.Probably the only unique thing about SG as a fighter that I've seen is the IPS (infinite prot system). If a combo reaches stage 5 and the same attack is used to open up the next loop that had been used in the previous stages the opponent will glow pink and can hit any attack to ""burst (GGXX)"" and end the combo. I've still seen doubles that have taken 90% of my HP in a no meter combo so I'm still unsure how this works.Fairly well constructed with GGPO lobby support, but the game still has a ways to go."
