,Recommended,245170,22350340,"Posted: 10 April, 2016",all,TheTeaBrewer,"Tell me if there is anything wrong with this review and I'll be sure to change itThis review is from the heart so its bound to be long as hellSkullgirls is a 2D fighting game in which every single penny is worth it's purchase price.This game was my first fighting game of this stature and probably THE best game for anyone wanting to get into the genre(We'll cover this later)The games first impression is a solid one as you're thrusted to the menu with some smooth♥♥♥♥♥jazz musicThe game has 3 main modes, the single player, the multi player, and the training modeThe single player includes, story mode, arcade mode, and a cpu quick match. The story mode provides a unique story depending on the character you choose, the lentgh of the story (for each character) can range from 15 minutes to an hour depending on the difficulty you are playing on (The Fukua story mode is a ♥♥♥♥♥!) which welcomes a good amount of play time. These characters are also charming in their own right as their personalities each differ and make for some pretty good story telling.Speaking of characters there are a total of 14 characters however 5 of them are DLC (1.99 Each) these characters each have their own unique playstyle which will be the preference to the player wheter they like grappling characters, combo characters, or characters that require stratagetic placement of their moves. This was a very welcoming feeling as I hardly felt that any to characters were the same(Besides Filia and Fukua).Each character also has 25 unique color palettes to choose from which really showed how much these devs cared about the culture nowadays and their product. Every time there was a color pallete based on another game and I was able to recognize that I immeadiatly said to myself ""Yeah these devs get me""The multi player is solid as all hell and I rarely ever saw the framrate dip because either me or the other player has a bad connection. Although the quick matches for some odd reason don't work all the time for me, the lobby matches worked perfectly. However if you dont practice enough with your prefered characters and deside to jump into a lets say a quick match you are going to get your♥♥♥♥♥beaten ALOT. As your opponent will rack up combos and combos and combos against you which is my only real issue with this game. Even though their is a built in mechanic where infinite combos aren't allowed I still found at times people were able to do such things (or I just suck)The biggest praise i have for this game is its extensive tutorials, these tutorials cover everything to standard movements, blocking, advanced techniques, mix ups, and even diving into specific characters with their movesets and how they play best. This tutorial is the very reason why this is the first game i recommend to anyone who wants to get into the genre.Stages are varied and are mesmerizing to look at, music is also funky to listen too even outside of the game, and frame rate is always consistent.This game is one of the best indie and best fighting game I have ever played. This game overall rightfully deserves a 9/10 from me.Thanks for reading"
