,Recommended,245170,8262831,"Posted: 24 December, 2013",all,priv_bryan,"First title from Lab Zero Games. This game honestly does not bring anything new to the table.You get what you pay for, and what you're paying for is one of the most solid fighters I've played in a good while.What it lacks in content more than makes up for it in robust gameplay consisting of custom assists, responsive controls, and a very diverse cast that comes with their own charm(boobies). Voice acting for the game has been done on a proffesional level, and it only adds to their character. All characters feel very different from the rest of the roster, each with a different focus. Different aspects of the game added to make it fair for newcomers and veterans such as infinity breaks. Even comes with a tutorial that sets you in the right path for technical play. This game was made for people who play fighting games by people who play fighting games, and they have done an amazing job balancing and crafting what could be a close to perfect title for anyone who enjoys the genre. Lab Zero is taking steps in the right stride, a stride that most triple A developers should be taking with their titles. Free DLC for a good 3 months when it's released, and love and care for the game they created.Not to mention the many set backs this studio has been recieving, with Konami on their♥♥♥♥♥and limited indie developer funds, these guys need a break. I honestly cannot wait for their next title, I'm most likely going to purchase.And yeah. It has boobs. Buy the game."
