,Recommended,245170,7922003,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,Archmage,"Skullgirls is a 2d fighting game with a cast exclusively populated by girls, an impressive art style (it's a mix between ""dark deco"" and BioShock's retro/showbiz style) and music by outstanding composers such as Michiru Yamane and Vincent Diamante. The game welcomes newcomers and accommodates veterans, with detailed tutorials and several innovative mechanics that help balance gameplay.After about 15 hours of gameplay I've beaten every story mode, completed every tutorial, and started learning Filia at an intermediate level. Thanks to a bunch of community resources available, I've been able to pick up some moderate-length combos and understand how to approach the basic metagame.It's definitely worth checking out. While there are several complex inputs like quarter-circles, dragon punches and 360s, the tutorials do a good job of easing people into learning them. If you've never played a fighter and want to try one, Skullgirls is the way to go."
