76561198062937701,Recommended,245170,13572592,"Posted: 24 December, 2014",all,海賊王 [skooma],"A somewhat new, and certainly note-worthy addition to the 2D fighting arcade genre.Not only can you tell how much work has been put into it (I've watched some of the Lab Zero live streams and can confirm), but there's a good system set up where you can not easily abuse an infinite combo chain.Well... unless you have no idea what you're doing or your skill does not even come close to matching up to that of your opponents.That is my only complaint about the game.It's a very addicting and fun arcade fighter, but I've come to a point where the CPU level is too easy even on Nightmare difficulty. When I switch over to online, you have people playing that are even more pathetically easy to beat, or they're the complete opposite and you are going against some ridiculously skilled opponent or spammer where you will not even be able to move a single bit the entire round due to being constantly attacked.Other than that, it's fun if you enjoy a challenge, and clean looking, and I've had no problems with frame rate or anything of the sort. Also boobs, if that really seems to be a key selling point for you.And Lab Zero still puts out DLC, so there's some great things to still look forward to."
