76561198066436824,Recommended,245170,19893190,"Posted: 23 December, 2015",all,The Flying Toaster,"Proving accessibility does not ruin a game’s depth, Skullgirls is an easy to learn, hard to master 2D fighter the has helped me, and many others get a foot in the door of a genre’s cult following. Including a cast of very creative, and diverse characters. Each with their own playstyles, story mode and canon in the jazzy, hostile world of New Meridian. However hostile the world is, the game is ready to ease you in it. With a tutorial that teaches basic fighting game vocabulary, and it’s character’s traits. While the DLC may include some characters that may be hard to play against if you don’t own the DLC, Skullgirls includes a “Endless beta” with all the DLC unlocked to learn each character's moves, and combos.Skullgirls is a fine game that helps include more players in a genre that may have seemed to complicated, or out of reach to people just starting out, While still providing the depth, and charm to make it it’s own."
