,Recommended,245170,13953947,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,SanicFax 2: Electric Boogaloo,"Alright, this is my first Steam review, but I'm used to doing this on other sites. Let me start by saying that Skullgirls is quite easily the greatest fighting game I have ever played, and that it ranks as #3 on my list of all-time favorite games, behind Team Fortress 2 and Final Fantasy X.Now that my fanboy session is over, let's get to the review. I will not say that Skullgirls is a perfect game. While I love it, just like loving a person, it's not perfect. Close, but no cigar. Other than a few unnecessarily difficult commands, the only thing I can legitimately say that I have a problem with is the painful amount of lag during online play. I have fairly decent hardware, so the game runs perfectly on my computer, but the first time I tried to play online with one of my friends, we both ended up with lag to the point that the timer would lower by a second after three seconds in reality. Honestly, this kind of pains me to say, but it is something that I do truly hate about Skullgirls. Otherwise, I hold this little slice of gaming heaven not just close to my heart, but against it. With my own prejudice set aside, I give Skullgirls a heartily thought-over 9.7 out of 10. Anytime somebody asks me for a game that I recommend to them, I have two immediate thoughts: Skullgirls, and Five Nights at Freddy's.And to you, wonderful developers, you probably won't end up seeing this, but I thank you, for giving us this unbelievably amazing game, and I hope that, in the future, we can help to Keep Skullgirls Growing.With heartfelt regards,Arrick Pearson"
