76561198041835319,Recommended,245170,14588176,"Posted: 21 February, 2015",all,EpeeSteven,"Now before I get started I would like to say that I don't play that many fighting games on a competative level aside from Smash Bros. I've played games like MvC3, Ki, and Mk9, which are all good but eventually got stale to me. So why in the holy f**k do I love Skullgirls so much?!?!  Skullgirls is an interesting one. It's like any normal fighting game, but with waifus. I'm not too sure what more of an explenation you would want but I think that's a good place to start. So what makes skullgirls so amazing? Well that would be everything, which currently includes intuitive gameplay, beautiful hand drawn visuals, an increadible and catchy soundtrack, it's easy to play but is complex enough to be mastered, brief, but interesting story modes for each character, a very in depth tutorial , TONS of lore, multiple clever references to memes and other games, fanservice, flashy and awe inspireing supermoves, the big middle finger to physics, and last but certainly not least, a cast of increadibly interesting and likeable characters. Seriously there is not one character in this game that I dont like to some extent, and while you could argue that this is because the roster is rather small (8 characters normally) this is more or less because it features DLC that adds in an extra 4 characters, with more constantly being made. Sooo yeah, Skullgirls. It's a great game with great developers, and a great fanbase. And it's only 15$, what more could you ask for? An outstanding 9/10 in my book."
