76561198098446171,Recommended,245170,9075545,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Rare Hunter Tenebrae,"One of my favorite 2-D fighters with well done, hand drawn characters and animations. The rooster consists of (at the moment) an all female cast that are unique fighters in their own way. No one character feels like a clone of each other and has a very distinct, over the top fighting style. The best feature of this game by far is the in game tutorial which teaches the player literally EVERYTHING about the game mechanics and character abilities. I have not seen a tutorial that thorough since DBZBT3 for the ps2. The combat is very fluid and responsive and as far as I can tell all the characters feel balanced. There isn't one overpowered character that just gets mained for the sake of winning ( looking at you UMVC3 cough wesker cough) so its entirely possible to play competitively with your favorite character ( my case squigly, fillia and peacock). I recommend it for anyone looking for a new fighter game or new players who want to learn general fighting game mechanics.  8/10."
,Recommended,245170,18544285,"Posted: 18 October, 2015",all,CyberBinary,"I have previously written a review for this game but I think it's time to make a new one. My goal is to make this easy to understand at a glance.GraphicsThis one is super opinion heavy and it's best to just judge for yourself.+Character sprites- The characters are all well drawn and stand out from everything on the screen. There are a ton of colors to choose from (over 20 per character) and many are references to other characters. The fanservice in this game can be seen as excessive, but I don't care about it or notice it much.+Stages- The stages, for the most part, look great. The stages are somewhat 3D (which can be changed in the options) but it isn't super noticeable. They all look like they were designed with a purpose; they don't look like they were just thrown in. Another good thing about the stages is that they never distract me from the game.+Animation- Everything is super well animated in this game. The attacks always look smooth and there are no animation-hitbox oddities such as the super large Street Fighter II Shoryuken hitbox.Gameplay+Team size selection- Skullgirls allows you to select the number of characters are on your team. Single character teams are viable in this game because each character in a multiple character team is weakened based on the team size.+Overall game feel- Everything in this game feels crisp and responsive. This is personal opinion, but it is one of the best feeling fighting games I've ever played.+Infinite Combo Prevention System- This game has a mechanic where it detects when the opponent is doing an infinite combo and allows the other player to break free. Because of this, one combo doesn't mean a immediate loss.+Assist selection- When selecting your characters, you can input normals and specials as assist moves. Since these aren't new moves, you will immediately know how they work. It also provides for options that are fun to test out.Tools for New Players+Great tutorial- The tutorial teaches you mechanics that are used in many other fighting games. There is also a section that teaches about each character individually.+Team selection makes the game easy to get into- You don't have to learn more than one character to start playing this game.+Great training room- Things like slow motion and showing hitboxes make it easy to understand the game's mechanics.+360 Detection- When doing a 360 motion, the game will prevent you from jumping during it.Concluding StatementsThis is one of the best fighting games I have ever played. I know that it won't be to everyone's tastes, but I find it very hard to think of places where this game is lacking. Many of the problems that people had were ironed out by the developers who continue to work on this game.  If you like games such as Marvel vs Capcom you are going to want to check this one out.If you are new to the fighting game genre and are interested in getting better, BUY THIS GAME!Just keep your expections high because this game is sure to surpass them."
