,Recommended,245170,21219597,"Posted: 14 February, 2016",all,Mr12000,"Really one of the most underrated fighting games to ever be released. I love watching the majors for this side event, because I'm always seeing something new. The art is incredible, the music is classic, the other sound design is nice and punchy, and the characers are some of the most unique and inspired I've ever seen. Sure, at it's core, it's a fighting game - reduce your opponent's HP to zero, and you win! But underneath, there are some many other mechanics at play. The infinite detection system, along with the later-added drama meter keeps the game honest and fair. Not only that, but it was then found out that you can bait your opponent to burst out of the combo and punish it, adding a whole new layer of meta to the original game.I really can't speak highly enough. With all the hours I've put in, I barely know a couple BnBs with all of the cast, and there's not even that many characters compared to other modern fighting games! On top of that, the almost literally limitless number of things you can do with assist characters is so fascinating - because you can choose ANY attack in your teammates arsenal to be an assist. Filia's cr.mk to extend a combo? You got it. Cerebella's anti-air command grab? Done. Eliza's hyper armor puppet attack? Yup!I understand that people want to pay as little as possible for things in general, but this is a game and studio that really DESERVES the full price tag. I've now purchased this game on Xbox 360, PC, and PS4/Vita. I like it that much. If you really want to pick it up on sale, go for it - it typically gets down to maybe $5 with all DLC. But either way, if you're interested in fighting games, this one will keep you engaged and thinking for hours."
