76561198006578878,Recommended,245170,33591978,Posted: 16 July,all,LN-Omega,"Make no mistakes, it's a fast, punishing and unforgiving game. There is little to no neutral game (but when there IS, it's SO REWARDING and intense), there are no comeback mechanics, combos are long (although people who played earlier versions will attest this got better) and resets are extremely varied and powerful. Your skills, and your skills alone will dictate whether you will win or lose, and you will lose a lot at first.But all this is the result of a small, but varied roster (gameplay wise) full of very powerful characters and strong fundamental mechanics. What little (so to speak) defensive options include unlimited pushblock, absolute guard and reversal options for all characters. When it comes to offensive options, though, sky is the limit. Cross-ups, high-low mixups, low to throw mixups, throws that are combo starters for pretty much every character, airthrows for everyone... The design philosophy here was to balance the game by making sure every character is reliable both on defense (sorta), but mostly on offense. That's a philosophy I wish most fighting games would embrace: Stop nerfing, make everyone great from the get go.The one downside I can imagine for this game is that he art-style might not please everyone. Else, I wholeheartedly give this game a 10/10. Would spend another 745 hours on it if they hadn't nerfed my main AGAIN."
