,Recommended,245170,30897672,Posted: 2 April,all,Maranasati,"+Awesome soundtrack; by far the best I've heard on a fighting game.+Voice acting on point.+Gorgeous to look at: unique, dark, Art-Deco anime.+Gloriously demented. Funny as hell.+Plenty of pop-culture references to delight your inner geek, without being cliche.+Plenty of fan-service to delight your inner perv.+Fast-paced controls. Simple to learn; hard to master.+Even has a useful, progressive tutorial. When was the last time we had that in a fighting game, or any game?+Excellent controller support: something that's all too rare in video games.+Combo system prevents infinite loops, making for far more unpredictable gameplay.+Couldn't find a single review among over eleven thousand with anyone criticizing the AI. How rare is that for a recent fighting game?Would heartily recommend.Looking likely to be my favorite fighting game of the past few years; possibly of all time!"
,Recommended,245170,33445409,Posted: 10 July,all,【ELITE✧Elder】,"This game has the greatest tutorial of all time, not just teaching you how to play this game, but giving solid tips on fighting games in general, it will teach you things you can apply to all other fighters, like SF or MK. I have two problems with this game, all normals can be linked into a combo, and combos last too long. It feels like if you hit someone you have a gaurenteed combo, and you can just wail on them for ever, being the combo-er feels like repeating the same combo over and over, and being the combo-ee feels like you could put your controller down and get a pizza by the time your opponent is done. The characters are awesome and deep, the stories make you feel for each character individually. The 2nd Encore dlc gives the story voices, something i think shouldve been there already, and includes all the dlc characters and colors. The dlc characters feel unbalanced, having too many strong options. Specifically i have a disliking for big band and Beowolf, big band is terribly boring to fight and feels like he just does too much damage, the combo potential on him is barely and upside against a good player. Beowolf feels monotonous to fight, having to sit through many pick up grabs and giant chair hitboxes, its just not so much fun. Overall the game is super fun and handles amazingly. 7/10 would reccomend."
