,Recommended,245170,17692961,"Posted: 24 August, 2015",all,亞 Doctor 亞,"Skullgirls is a nice 2-D fighting game which puts a nice twist on the old formula. It's controls are intuitive and smartly designed with punches and kicks neatly sorted over the buttons in almost a stacked manner. Each attack for both punches and kicks has a light, medium, and heavy attack. Each character Different from eachother and even made a nice ""copycat"" character named Double which mimics bits and pieces from all the characters rather than randomly selecting one characters moveset at random like in other games like Tekken. Great detail was put in the background and is hard to miss. For example, every Background is animated with a total of 5 frames for minor things like characters, but smoother for moving backgrounds. Also a nice thing to note is that some characters aren't permanent residents in backgrounds, it constantly changes everytime you play recycling characters. Online multiplayer is fun too, there's always someone willing to fight you in ""Quick match"" and you can usually find an open lobby in regular matches. The only negative thing about competitive is that some people take it way to seriously and either practice super hard to find a combo that will get by the combo breaking system or cheat by adding a macro which does all the work for them in order to get a higher rank. Overall Skullgirls is an interesting game which makes up for a lack of many characters by making everyone of them so unique that battles never lose their fun. 10/10 in my book."
