,Recommended,245170,17961381,"Posted: 9 September, 2015",all,Bojangles4th,"I really like Skullgirls, and that's saying something; especially considering I don't really like most fighting games anyways.IMPORTANT: Great for beginners to fighting games, as this quite possibly has one of the best tutorials for a game I've used.   If you're new to fighting games ( like I was / and still am, kinda ) some movements will be noticeably more difficult to pick up at first, ( like the Z shape type movements ) but you'll realize the accuracy for said movements isn't as high if you're using it in a combo string, so tip: If you are going to string a Z type movement attack, do it during a string; it's less harmful to be slightly off in movement.In Singleplayer, I love that all of the characters have their own story, and how they all relate to each other in one way or another; it has kind of a dark noir tone to it, but isn't afraid to be silly once in a while.   I was actually surprised a few times throughout ( most notably: Eliza, Filia, Big Band; at least IMO )      But I recommend playing through each of them on Medium-Hard ( Warning: Hardest is arguably Eliza ) so you can gradually and more naturally pick up the game mechanics.In Multiplayer, I've only played Quick Match 2-3 times, and each time I got bodied by an infini-string player joining Beginner level lobbies ( seriously m8? ) so I stuck to Lobby play with friends until I learned a medium-long string with a couple characters, and am currently working on applying assists.The Charactersare all very unique, except Fukua.  I don't like Fukua.   (Triggered)  They have pretty expressive personalities, with the calmer of the bunch probably being Squigly and Parasoul.The Balanceis also amazing, but do note that it's pretty agreed Painwheel is probably the worst in the game in general.   Again, the balance is amazing, so she's still good, just that everyone else is probably better in a minorly significant way.The Artworkis also visually impressive, pretty eye-candy; the animations are very smooth and fluid, and the particles are not overdone.The Soundtrackis also very nice, with my personal favorite stages being Under the Bridge and Maplecrest (in that order)-----------------------Overall, I'd give the game an 8/10, though I do recommend getting the DLC for it.*Gamepad or Fight-Stick highly recommended"
