,Recommended,245170,8581445,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,8Bit64,"Coming from someone who never had any interest in fighting games, I love this game. It's so easy to learn the basics you'll be amazed how fast you go from button masher to actually knowing effective combos. The tutorials in this game are so good that you'll feel a little bit cheated that your $60 AAA fighter didn't have extensive explanations like these. From walking and basic moves to hitstun, mixups and hit confirmations, even if those last three sounded like complete gibberish to you, you'll know all about it and how to utilize it in well under an hour. Controls are easy to bind to whatever controller, joystick, gamepad, fightstick, power glove or keystroke you'd like. Once you're all hooked up, the game is as smooth as butter to play, making no real issues in that department.The visual style is one of the best I've seen an it's ultimately what hooked me right off the bat. As a big animation junkie I have to say, these 2D character drawings are so well animated, you'd never believe it was an indie title. The stages are well crafted and the characters doubly so. The attention to detail is so outstanding, the flow of it is a pleasure to see and if you pay attention as you go along, you'll find more and more little things that will make you admire the hard work put into it all.It's a classic fighting game trope to not care about the story mode, but damnit, it's actually interesting and doesn't feel like some tacked-on we-only-did-this-because-we-had-to, half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥attempt. The dark and twisted backstory leaves alot of questions unanswered and when you've played through every character's storyline you'll actually give a♥♥♥♥♥♥ Imagine that.On an auditory level, (ha) this game isn't a slouch either. The music is catchy and the voicework is great too. There aren't a huge ammount of different lines, but they're good enough that you'll get a little bundle of glee when you hear your favorite one uttered after a match is over.The one bad thing I have to say about this game is the fact that it's not popular enough yet. From what I've seen, the community is still growing so you may not find anyone on your level in the online, especially if you're new to the genre. It's a shame, because there's so many references to the community, other fighting games, anime, cartoons and internet culture it's always a treat when you spot one. There's a stage where there's sometimes a dog dressed like Guile and Chun li. Do I really need to persuade you more to buy this game after you just read that?Though playing alone is fine for awhile, I would gighly suggest playing with people you know. Buy a few copies for a friend or two and go play this great fighter. If you're looking to get into the fighting genre, already into it and want to play a high-quality one, into animation or just really like animated boobs, I would recommend you buy this game. Support an awesome game and make the growing community even greater!"
