,Recommended,245170,9265942,"Posted: 25 February, 2014",all,Pet Food,"Skullgirls is a well-rounded, well-balanced 2D fighter with a roster of memorable characters. There's little overlap between characters (save for the ""joke"" character Fukua and Filia), but team mechanics can be manipulated to make any of these freakshows a threat.With a solid tutorial system and a community that thrives on teaching new players how to be successful, Skullgirls is probably the best entry to the world of fighting games. Many of the techniques used in this game translate to other games, but if you're not versed in the genre it's very easy to pick up and learn the combos needed to be successful. Once you have the muscle memory you'll be nailing your opponents to the wall.Online play tends to be a bit unforgiving, but lobby play lets you find players of similar caliber and hone your skills.Definitely recommended to anyone interested in exploring fast-paced fighting games."
