,Recommended,245170,19786178,"Posted: 19 December, 2015",all,LambdaCalculus379,"Skullgirls was a tremendous and pleasant surprise for me! Although I am not a huge fighting game player nowadays, I was huge into them in my younger days. I went into Skullgirls not expecting much of anything, but everything so far has blown that skepticism right out of the water!Skullgirls plays like a blend of Marvel Vs Capcom 2 (frantic pace, team mechanics) with some Guilty Gear (combos and move execution) blended together. It's fast and furious, thoroughly addicting, and long lasting! It's also absolutely gorgeous to watch, especially in 1080p, with its ""Dark Deco"" look, vivid colors, and buttery smooth, hand animated sprites! And its soundtrack, co-composed by Castlevania alumnus Michiru Yamane, is jazzy, Gothic, and rife with very CV-esque vibes, and proves that jazz can perfectly work in a fighting game. That character select theme will earworm into your brain for days!Is the game worth it? Oh, hells yes! Just get the DLC packs with it for the extra characters; the default lineup is a bit sparse, and about this game's only major flaw."
