76561198034778236,Recommended,245170,11339721,"Posted: 20 July, 2014",all,DrMeow,"Skullgirls is a fantastic fighting game with wonderfully unique visuals.Pros: Graphics, Sound, ControlsCons: Story, GameplaySkullgirls reigns almost unmatched for its style and graphics.  Every one of the high-definition, hand-drawn characters looks absolutely stunning; the quality is almost unbelievable.  From the opening music to the announcer's ""Showtime!' the sound is excellent.  The keyboard works surprisingly well for a fighting game, but the controller still bests it, and beyond that, the arcade pad reigns supreme.Despite its excellent assets, the story is lackluster: people fighting over a powerful artifact.  The amount of fanservice doesn't mesh well with the fact that the artifact empowers only women.  Similar to how a writer may end with 'it was all a dream,' the ending is lazily tacked on.  As new IP, some consulting would have worked wonders and hopefully developers aren't afraid to retcon the rough edges.Skullgirls' tutorial is by far the best among all the fighting games, but still not enough to condition new players.  Fighting games in general need to fix this problem or continue to lose popularity: having to slog through a couple hours of practicing the same combo over and over again is not 'fun' and doesn't feel like 'improvement.'Skullgirls manages to be both a strong introduction for beginners and an intricate game purpose-built for veterans.8/10"
