,Recommended,245170,7933552,"Posted: 5 December, 2013",all,Zelotus,"Description:-Inspired by the old 2d fighting games. Skullgirls is one of the best out there. It follows the path of currently 9 girls on their quest for the infamous Skullheart. The skullheart will fill them with their darkest and deepest desires. Having to fight their way to get it. You can fight in a match consisting of a player party of 1,2, or 3 people. Each varying assist moves and balanced strength depending on how many people you choose to fight with.Controls:-Standard arcade format, closely similar to street fighter, with low,mid, and high punches and kicks.-Compatability with keyboard, console controler, or arcade joystick.-Easy to learn, even for casual gamers not used to fighters. As most characters share the same combinations for   blockbusters and special moves.Pros:-Fast pace-Fun for high skill and low skill players-Unique artstyle and music-Unique and original characters with their own personalityCons:-Not many players online to find a match with. If you're looking for a match it's easier to go into ranked matches, but this isn't reccomended for low skill/casual players.-Servy laggy at times-Not a huge character selection as compared to Mortal Kombat or Street Fighter or Marvel Vs. Capcom-There isn't a reliable combo breaker, you can literally be infinite combo'd after someone hits you once.-Fighting games aren't for everyone, it is a dying breed of games and the player-base will always be low. So find/make friends who own this game to always have someone to play with."
