,Recommended,245170,1471470,"Posted: 25 August, 2013",all,hybridial,"Skullgirls is one of the most impressive achievements in animation I've seen in videogames in a long time (outside of Vanillaware's work anyway) and is brimming excessively with personality and inventiveness, as well a sensible and level headed approach to the genre. This head also sports a giant pair of fists.Skullgirls makes execution easy so that even those relatively new to the genre can get right into it and start learning the real ins and outs of playing a fighting game. Though its roster is currently small every character is deep, full of possibilities and are above all, memorable. Be it the grappling power of Cerebella, the charge techniques of Squigly or the projectile spamming cartoon addict, Peacock, every battle in Skullgirls is exciting and hype fuelled.My experience of playing the game online with others in Europe has been smooth, but I can't comment on the online beyond that unfortunately. Still, for the price this game has a bargain and has four more free DLC characters due to be released to enhance it's already strong roster."
