,Recommended,245170,24069007,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,dirty nimrod,"Now a lot of the reviews of this game are just people saying which character they like or is ""their waifu"" without giving any info of the actual GAME. When I was looking for an actual review of the game to see what I would need to know, I was left completely in the dark. As a noobie to this game, I think I can offer some advice to other fellow noobies just picking up the game or even people thinking about buying it (which you TOTALLY should buy this game).Now starting off I would reccomend that you play this game with an arcade stick/pad, as it, along with most fighting games of this nature, are practically near IMPOSSIBLE to adjust to without one. Playing with a controller may be appealing to some but DONT use a keyboard. So, in short, Arcade Stick > Controller > Keyboard.Next, I would suggest going to the training center to learn everything that there is to know, the devs really put some time and effort into making a new player feel welcome and it shows. It may feel discouraging to keep messing up on a single action at first (especially the super moves), but you will get the hang of it.Finally, I'd reccomend that you play with every single character to start off and see who you like and fits your playstyle. Just choosing the character with the biggest tiddys or the most revealing clothes won't do you any favors except to your willy.Now I know this isn't much of a review of the game as it is just advice of how to start but I truly think that noobies and people willing to buy this are alone in the dark when it comes to advice, sorry for sounding like an episode of Neds Declassified School Survival Guide guys.But, if you're still on the fence about this game, I'd just like to list off a few other great traits that this game has to offer:-Amazing and Fluid Animation-Art that will blow your MIND-CRAZY COMBOS-Unique cast of characters-INSANELY GOOD Soundtrack-Intriguing PresentationIf I'm being honest and non-comedic, I'd give this game an 8.7/10. Not as good as Smash Bros and Marvel vs Capcom, but cooler than Street Fighter and Tekken imo.sorry for the wall of text and rambling"
