,Recommended,245170,7905838,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,Zeke,"While this may not look like a mechanics fighter on the front, Skullgirls has a combat system worthy of (and has been in!) tournament play. This game can be quite the learning curve if you are new to fighter games (like myself), but once you learn the way combos and super moves work, it is an amazing experience. Most fights boil down to fraction-of-a-second button and stick combination, but once you get a feel for it, you can be devastating. Of course, this game is just as fun playing with friends casually on a lazy afternoon alongside Smash Bros, or placing bets and fighting it out! I totally recommend you use a controller, I use a USB xbox 360 controller, but Skullgirls also supports those 6-button USB fighter pads, which some of my friends have.With it's unique gameplay mechanics, art style, character stories, and a development team dedicated to listening to the community, Skullgirls is a game I recommend any hardcore or casual gamer to pick up."
