76561198013127756,Recommended,245170,33965588,Posted: 2 August,all,Conman540,"Definitely my favorite fighter of all time.It's fun and fast paced, but not so fast that it's impossible to keep up. The animations are so clean and beautiful. The voice acting is very fitting and never dulls out, even after hours of play. The combos are satisfying to pull off and learn. I really wish this got more love than it did, because my biggest problem is a majority of the people you will face online have owned this game for quite a while. Only the diehard fans are around anymore, so it drives away new players because of the HUGE skill gap. If you can power through it and learn the game and characters like I did, you'll be able to enjoy this game much more than you would without the training. If you aren't the kind of person to want to learn the game to enjoy it more, then it would only really be worth the buy if you're okay with fighting AI and getting stomped online. I can't really blame the game itself for the skill gap, because it's a high skillcap game. You always have to be aware of your opponent and try to be one step ahead. I love mindgames and this game is full of them. Also has one of the best tutorials I've seen in a long time. It also has one of the best training modes, so you can test any situation you can imagine.I have no idea how to end a serious review so I'll just kinda say it's 500% worth your money if you don't mind a few hours in training mode."
,Recommended,245170,23077309,"Posted: 19 May, 2016",all,Rumpus,"Whether you're new to fighters, or a veteran at them, this is a game I highly recommend for anyone wanting to try. The story is a strong point, it holds the original ""Fight for the x"" type story, but with more depth. I do wish there were more introductions before just plainly jumping into a battle however. And then we touch on the gameplay.COMBOS!!!This game tenders a lot more to raw skill, so expect your butt to be royally kicked when playing online. Combos are harsh, and usually whoever can get one another in a 50-hit combo will be expecting a victory in no time. There's not really much of a breaker-type ability, just counters, pokes and blocks.CharactersThe strictalbeit sexycharacters are no short of vibrant personalities and traits, like the schoolgirl Filia, who has a parasite living on her head acts as majority of her attacks, and the cartoony Peacock, who has a squad of various characters and has attacks like you would see in Loony Toons.Part of the charm of this game (and most other fighters) is finding which character is right for you. There are TONS of attacks and fighting styles, although they are broken up into categories like  light kicks and heavy punches.IMPORTANT MESSAGEThe one flaw (for me at least) is that this game is incredibly hard to play without a joystickinsert joke about sexy female fighters hereSo I would highly recommend using one or getting one, so that the combos later on are actually doable. Controllers work too, but seeing as there are 6 main attack buttons, plus directional movement and an additional 2 or 3, it'll be a mess on one.Final Thoughts + ScoreSkullgirlsis a unique fighting game with a great story, solid characters and extraordinarily fun gameplay. Combos can be a bit touchy at times, but it makes up for it in gameplay. I would recommend to anyone who is a fan of fighters, or newcomers.Characters? 9Story? 8Gameplay? 9Replay Value? 8.5Overall?9 / 10."
