76561198061565121,Recommended,245170,9910910,"Posted: 23 April, 2014",all,Red Delta11,"I heavily recommend this game.  Skullgirls is not only one of the best non-street fighter fighting games on steam, it is one of the best fighting games out there period. The gameplay is more reminscant of Marvel vs Capcom 2 and KoF then Street Fighter, but any SF player will easily catch onto the mechanics of the game. To answer some peoples questions about whether or not this is a beginner friendly game, well it kinda is and isn't. You will definitely need a gamepad, you cannot hope to play any fighting game with a keyboard. I would recommend picking up a SFxT ps3 gamepad, as it has a 6 button face and is fully pc compatible. At the time of this writing it is on amazon for under 20$ and is perfect if you want to play a fighting game without investing in a fightstick. The online community, while relatively friendly, is filled with fighting game vets like myself. Do not expect to just jump in online and win, you will have to spend time in the tutorial, training, and arcade modes before even attempting online play. Overall I give this game a 9/10Also don't buy vanguard princess"
