76561198030237905,Recommended,245170,7857271,"Posted: 30 November, 2013",all,Pytor Mortis,"A really good take on old, fast paced, 2D fighting games, with a rather small, but unique roster of characters. Unique both in design and fighting style.The art is very beautiful, some might be turned down by the obvious anime influences, but that's just personal taste. Backgrounds are very pleasing to the eye, as well as animations. 1400 sprites of animation per character? Yes sir.Characters are, like I mentioned above, very interesting both to look at and play. Some might say, that they're oversexualized, and he would be correct. However, most of them are as much sexualized as they are scary. Example: you have your normal catgirl type of character, yet at the same time, she is basically a zombie. She can detach her head and attack enemies with it, and so forth.They aren't damsels in distress, so me personally, I don't mind this particular character design.Tutorials are fabulous. Useful both for beginners and pros, they explain pretty much everything. Not only how different characters combo work, but also the very basics of practically every fighting game. Just like tutorial should be.On the other hand, small roster is a bit of a nuiscance, but this will be fixed with additional characters. For free, for a certain amount of time, which is really nice. That's... pretty much all I can think of when it comes to downsides. From a technical point of view, again, some people might consider the art style and the overall ""feel"" of this title as something unbearable.If you find this okay, though, then wait no more and check this out, it's definitely worth your time."
