,Recommended,245170,9075890,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Noob.dec,"In short: Skullgirls is a classically styled 2D fighter in the a vein similiar to the MVC series. When I say it is classically styled, I mean that in more ways than one; the gamplay is reminscent of a blend of KoF, Street Fighter 2, MVC, and a dash of Tekken, the music is all Jazz and Blues influenced, and the opening of matches is themed like a '40s movie. If you are unfamiliar with fighting games, the game features an extremely in-depth tutorial series. More advanced players will dominate online matches; don't even think you will win a match until you've logged close to 50 hours. The story, arcade, and survival modes are, in my opinion, enough to justify buying the game on sale ,but if you are confident in your online abilities, then it is easily worth full price."
