,Recommended,245170,5630954,"Posted: 3 September, 2013",all,Iron Shief,"Really fun game. Tight control, nice combos, a little hard on keyboard, but manageable. Would recommend using a arcade fightstick though. This is my first arcade fighter and it's really cool how the teach you everything, seriously, the tutorials super in depth. It was a little hard to get into at first, but once you dive in, the different combos that you pull off feels awesome, and the best part, you actually accomplished it. Yes you, not some one button press mindless shooter, but actually you, you pulled off a combo and with that got the advantage. This is a game that is rewarding in its challenges.A rare feature in the fighting genre is the balancing of teams. Skullgirls allows you to fight as a team of 1 to 3 characters against 1 to 3 characters. This means that you can go badass and fight 3 enemies with just a Cat gir- pers- woma- thing. Now, you might think that in multiplayer matches, that would be unfair, but Skullgirls designed the fighting to be handicapped. The less characters on your team, the stronger they are. That means that if you have one character and your opponent has a team of two, your fighter is more than twice as strong (health and attack wise) as your opponents, same thing goes for three characters. This is because have more than one character on you team allows you to switch out each of them, letting them ""rest"" to heal up and allows for team assit moves.Excited about all the DLC characters which are free when they first come out BTW. I started pretty bad at the game, but gotten to an adiquite level. This game is frequently updated so some things might change over time, but I'm sure Skullgirls will stay Skullgirls at heart.Honestly though, I'm not gonna be the guy who nags you to buy this, I'm just saying why I like it. This is my favorite fighting game, also note, I'm a cheap guy. I never buy games at full price, but this game. This is the only game I've every gotten full price the day it came out. I was that hyped about it. The developers who update this game every 30 minutes are awesome as well, they listen to their fans instead of changing something and having no consent.The Good:-(Currently) attractive all girl fighters-Awesome combos-Game that makes you feel good about how you played-Breath taking art style, game is really gorgeous-In depth tutorial so you don't feel lost as what to do-Team set ups that allow 1 to 3 character teams-Did I mention pulling off combos is AWESOME?Sadly, the Bad:-""Infinity combo breaker"" is buggy- Due to their fighting styles, some characters are like Ro, Sham, Bo with one another-uninteresting and short campaigns, think Mortal Kombat with beautiful art-controls are really confusing to rebind-small amount of combos are hard to execute on keyboard ( Full Circle LP+LK? are you kidding me?)-argueable ""over powered"" characters (Cerabella's lvl 1 blockbuster can take out 75% of your health with the right conditions)TL;DR- This game is a hell of a drug."
