,Recommended,245170,8713865,"Posted: 15 January, 2014",all,Owari-no-splee,"Skullgirls is a pretty solid fighting game that has a really jazzy soundtrack teamed with a unique, hand-drawn art style. The game   sadly only has 8 playable characters (excluding DLC) to start off with but each character has a diffrent feel with their game play. In terms of story, each character has their own motives for searching for the ""Skull Heart"", the object of power that grants any girl's wish, so long as they are pure of heart. While one character may be looking to recover their past (Filia), another may be looking for their own salvation and free-will (pain wheel). Each character's story made me feel for them until their chapter closed. The game play is where the game shines. Each character has a diffrent fight style but yet they flow smoothly in actual fights and pulling off combos and special ""Block-Buster"" moves feels pretty good. A controler is somewhat suggested for the PC adaptaion because it would feel more natural and pulling off a really good block buster may requite making a full 360 rotation and using the arrow keys feels a bit awkward. The achivements are a bit of a pain to get but they are not IMPOSSIBLE. The game play is fun, the music is up beat, the graphics are cartoony (Which I love) but if you want 100% complete the game, achivements and all, a bit of patience is required."
