,Recommended,245170,9465057,"Posted: 14 March, 2014",all,Menax,"In incredibly fun, recognisable, and fast 2-D brawler. Whether you're new to the brawler scene and want to get into the genre, or just want to play a brawler to try it out, or a veteran of the scene and want something new and chalanging to learn that requires skill to fully master, Skullgirls can accomodate both.With it's classy art-style, unique atmosphere, comedy, and dark undertones, Skullgirls has an interesting world which varies from beautiful utopias, dark city streets, misterious labs, and haunting crypts, which is complimented by the exellent soundtrack that works perfectly with the rest of the game.Though there are few characters in comparison to other brawlers, they're all that are needed as each character is completely unique, and have a specific style to themselves. Each character takes a long time to master, even though the basics are easy to grasp thanks to the exellent tutorial system, and if you're playing online or in arcade mode, you can change the colour of your character with unlocked skins, which all have little refrences to other games and TV shows.The combat system is fun to play, fun to watch, and doesn't allow for endless combos like most brawlers, and while making it hard for button-mashers to prevail in a fight, it doesn't make it hard for the average player either.Overall, it is a very entertaining game, and is dirt cheap for the quality, and recieves constant updates. Even if you're not particularly interested in brawlers, it's worth buying just to have on your shelf for the option, maybe even play it in-between other games casually.9.5/10"
