76561198041995956,Recommended,245170,13970080,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,bahamut66,"Let me make something clear before we continue.  You CAN enjoy Skullgirls if you are not great at fighting games.  After all, I did.  However, this game is very offense heavy and you need to be aggressive to have any hope of success in vs.The game is beautiful, the animation is fluid, and the backgrounds and art style pop with a huge amount of detail.  Would have liked the story to be clearer and the art style itself is a bit hit or miss.  Lots of fan service so if you're not into that, well...maybe you should look elsewhere.  There is a very in depth tutorial, though, so even newbies can learn the basics of each character pretty easily.The biggest complaint I have with the game is the final boss, which is ridiculously cheap and difficult for beginners.Fighting games are not my forte and I have a few issues with this game, but on the whole, I do recommend it.  Just remember, the art style might not be for you and if you aren't a hardcore fighting game fan, you might not get as much out of it as others."
