,Recommended,245170,11081331,"Posted: 5 July, 2014",all,Rough Stone,"Skullgirls is a great fighting game with a storyline that's mysterious but easily understood as you progress the story and manages to be deeper than ""world wide fighting tournament"". The early 20th century ambience is atypical but not an unwelcome change as jazz beats and swing betray the usual grindy techno of other fighters. Not to mention the 2D art is beautiful and fluid and a refreshing change of pace from sprites and 3D models.The gameplay is accessible but with a high skill cap meaning online play can be pretty brutal but the story mode alone is worth it (not to mention playing with your more casual friends). If you're confident though online can be a fun place to be as long as you don't let the roughly 1 in 3 players that can land absurd combos bother you."
