,Recommended,245170,7812196,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,Jabberwockxeno,"SKullgirls is a fun and challenging game with a lot of personality.The premise is simple: There's a mystic artfiact that can grant wishes, but corrupts those who use it if they are not pure of heart, and various factions fight over it.However, the game's art style and matching personalility really makes this typical plot line into a non issue. Every character has myriad influneces, from other fighting characters (Painwheel takes after voldo), to genres (peacock is a homage to early cartoons, such as Popeye and Steamboat Willie).Addittionaly, the game has a huge amount of lore and backstory present in it, There is already over 40 characters with wiki pages and in universe concepts present on the wiki, despite the game (currently) only having 9 playable characters. Speaking of the story, I have found myself feeling emotionally invested in some of the characters, despite each character's story line only being a 30 minute ordeal.As far as actual combat, I feel it's a very good fighter. I'm no expert, but I can tell it has the deep mechanics and skill required for fighting game pros, but without feeling overly intmidating or difficult for more casual players. Combos don't feel stiff with very small windows of time to add on hits, specials are simple to pull off, but despite all of this, there really is a lot of depth.I highly reccomend skullgirls for just about anyone, unless they have a passionate hatred for the genre."
