76561198000262994,Recommended,245170,9912052,"Posted: 23 April, 2014",all,Pengowen,You should get this!  It's good! We can play it together!
,Recommended,245170,10301741,"Posted: 31 May, 2014",all,Scraping Coltrane Off Folkfuck,"LOOK AT 'EM ♥♥♥♥♥♥S!But all joking aside, this game is the perfect gateway for people who are new to the fighting genre thanks to the incredible tutorial and how quickly can one get used to the gameplay. However, this does not mean that just anyone can pick up the gamepad/keyboard/fightstick and instantly get good like in Super Smash Bros. or Marvel VS Capcom, no.Hardcore fighting gamers are going to love how many different ""ultra-long"" combos can they come up with, even though the game gives the beaten-up opponent the option to instantly break ""endless"" combos (in context, this is when the attacker only does the same serie of combos over and over again without diversity in his or her moves). So not only does the game enthuse diverse creativity in combos, it also gives a chance to free yourself from spamming.The artwork is uncannily pretty. Not only in the character designs, but in the way they move and punch around.Each character is unique in its own way and has its own attributes (yes, even the joke ""clone"" character ""Fukua"" which was added after positive response from an April Fool gag by Lab Zero). My personal favourites are Peacock, Valentine and the DLC character Squigly.The controls are exactly what you expect from a Capcom-like fighting game: easy to get by. However, my only complaint is that if a keyboard is the only controller available to you, you are going to have a REALLY hard time executing ""full-circle"" attacks (with a gamepad, you are supposed to to a 360 rotation with the joystick).However, if you expect this game to have a great single player mode, keep in mind that while there IS a story mode, it is only worth playing to unlock some of the alternate skins for the fighters. Unlike Super Smash Bros. Brawl's Subspace Emissary which arguably was a whole different game, or Injustice's story mode which felt like watching some sort of Justice League special episode, the Skullgirls story mode is pretty weak for most of the non-DLC characters. I'm serious, the fighters with the most interesting storylines were Squigly and Big Band, which aren't even in the core game. But hey, most people buy fighting games for the Versus mode, so in the end this really isn't a major issue.The last thing I am going to tell you about isn't really about the game itself, but about the DLCs. When a new character comes out, it will be free for three months. That means if you bought the base game before or during it's free availabilty, you can still keep it afterwards! Sadly if you did not buy the base game during that time, the DLC's price will rise depending on the time passed since release. This is a tactic to enthuse people to buy the game as early as possible.To conclude, I am going to give this game a big, solid 9/10 for the amazing gameplay, the diverse character roster and the great art. Really worth the $15."
