,Recommended,245170,8637423,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,Makerrcat,"A solid fighter with interesting mechanics, a small but decent (and growing) cast of characters to choose, a fair enough story, and an interesting art style. Now I know that might sound mediocre to some, but I only state it that way as if you had no interest in fighters before well I doubt this game will change your mind. Now if you DO have an interest in fighters there's a heck of a lot to keep you entertained and I would consider this game a must buy.Positives:+Controls feel very smooth and very tight. Not floaty whatsoever.+Characters are very interesting and very unique. Which is important considering the relatively small cast it has currently.+Tutorial is awesome and noob friendly. A very VERY nice feature for those trying to get into the fighting genera but unsure where or even how to start.+Tag team system is unique balanced and downright awesome. You can choose to fight matches as one really strong character, two semi-strong characters, or three sorta week characters, whom you can swap between during the fight MVC style. So being able to swap between any one or two characters, or have either one or two assist, or just go it alone, adds a ton of variation to the gameplay making this one heck of an experience worth playing again, and again, and again, and....Negatives:+Small cast of characters+Stable version (IE Not beta) currently only has no male characters.+Sexualisation is a little heavy, some might call sexist. Personally I find it to just be a matter of style, and in some ways they almost play it ironically, but it's all a matter of taste and I know some people really don't like this sort of thing which is why I put it here.I know at the beginning of this review I said I wouldn't call it anything to really give your attention to if you've never had an interest in fighting games to begin with. However, if you've ever even been slightly curios about the genera then I will say that this is probably the hands down best place to start.This has been Makkercat, and we're done here."
