,Not Recommended,245170,23960676,"Posted: 30 June, 2016",all,Suchgamesmuchplay on Twitch,"i know what everyone is going to say:'you've only got 4 hours under your belt, you dont know the game blah blah blah'well seeing as the steam description says: 'making the genre enjoyable and accessible to newcomers' my opinion should also be reccomened.first, some basic pro's/cons:pros:-unique characters-great art style-jazzy soundtrack to fit the game-inexpensive DLC (thank god)thats about itcons:-newcomers to side scrollers NOT welcome-infinite combo chains, getting to around 30 at least-tutorial doesnt give a steady input to each character, instead gives you each character info at chapter 7-story is boring, a literall 'tap enter' fest.-over sexualised characters and (im seriously not kidding when a flashy nurse costume is someones DEFAULT gear)-cutscenes, while they look pretty, are just pictures scrolling.-only way to have fun is with a friend-when a game gives a hitbox visible training option, you know your in for something.now, onto the deeper look at the pro's/cons:PROSthe characters are anything but your cookie cutter fighters. each has his or her own playstyle, so Parasol for the slower players, Ms.Fortune for the faster players and Peacock for the ranged people. i personally like painwheel for the combo strings and the cheesy backstory.art style looks like an awesome web-comic or an ask blog, which gives a very good cartoony feel to some characters (like peacock) and adds to the macabre of others (like Valentine)music is poppy and jazzy (ive always had a weak spot for that music)DLC when on sale is around 50p and is usually a new character, while now-a-days you gotta pay £5+CONS:this aint street fighter or mortal kombat. well, if you took street fighter and made it 10X harder because cetain staples of a good side scrolling fighter are missing, you got skullgirls. this game, as said before, states that it is 'making the genre enjoyable and accessable to newcomers'. this does not do that in any way. instead, it SHOULD say: 'new to these type of games? if so, dont touch this.'the issue of 'infinite combo chains' has always been in games like this, and has been easy to fix: just make the opponent invulnerable after a certain number or tweak the hitboxes for the spammable combo's to make them non-spammy. this, however, is next to none, and if you mess up 1 time in a match you might as well quit. ive been literally locked into combo's which have hit 30 hits or more and i can do next to nothing about it. in the air? no type of dodging or block if your hit. on the ground? better have frame perfect precision. and, i know this game was made in 2013, but its recent update was on the 25th of june. 5 DAYS AGO. get your shizz together.the tutorial seems ok, but the fact that it doesnt introduce the roster until chapter 7 bugs me. introduce them after the basics for god sakes! movement, attacking, blocking, throwing, specials, characters. NOT everything in the game that you can do THEN characters.story. only one's i have played is painwheel, peacock and parasol. painwheels was delightfully cheesy, and i found it honestly funny when she fought herself in her head. peacock was a genetic experiment. parasol is some cop lady. literally all i got from the tap Z fest of the cutscenes. they had a budget to use fully animated sprites in the majority of the game so why not in the cutscenes?! at least then you'd have something to look at.speaking of something to look at, the over, sexualization of most the characters. biggest and most obvious ones are Valentine (a nurse with more jiggle physics than beach volleyball games) and parasol (who is apparantly too poor to buy a longer jumper. literally panty shot in most moves). this is not apparant in characters like parasol, painwheel, ms. fortune (who is the only loveable character there due to her comical 'om nom nom' move) but characters like cerebella and filia are still sexualised, cerebella wearing a bottom of boobs only top and is continuously hunched foreward and filia's down middle kick move in a SERIOUSLY provocative manner. now im not complaining about this to the point of 'NO BOOBS! NO SEXY! ALL FULL CLAD IN CLOTHING!' in fact im the opposite: if a character is supposed to seem flirty, thats ok. but it seems as if the developers took a little TOO long on the jiggle physics, nudge nudge.go online, get♥♥♥♥♥whooped by a 50-80 long combo streak. get up, it happens again, rinse an repeat. only way to have fun is with a friend. nuff said.finally, if the negative reviews are coming from people with less than 30 hours in the game, yet posative reviews are coming from people with 100+ hours and your game says its for newcomers and veterans, theres something wrong.ps.i played with a friend. me painwheel, he peacock. i used combo's. he buttonmashed. i only JUST won by a single match. GG skills, GG."
