,Not Recommended,245170,12976894,"Posted: 16 November, 2014",all,Llama,"I don't like Skullgirls.Whilst the tutorial and artstyle is pretty good, you really need something similar to a Sega Saturn controller to play it, as today's standard gamepads aren't particular good for eight-directional output, and using shoulder buttons as extra main buttons (not the macro buttons) is awkward at best.Here's the thing though; even with one, the game, in my opinion isn't fun. It requires a high technical amount of skill to even beat the story mode on easy (which suffers from the classical unfair final boss which most fighters have), which honestly isn't every enjoyable at all. I can't even imagine attempting to playing this online due to how high the skill floor is to play as well.All in all, from a casaul point of view, I do not recommend playing Skullgirls. However, if you are relatively experienced at fighting games and have a lot of free time, it might be worth picking this up; I suggest reading other reviews for this sort of opinion."
