76561198022088968,Recommended,245170,7860461,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,somedude1013,"There is sooo much to say about this game but i'll try to keep this short and simple1. Gameplay: The gameplay welcomes both newbies with fighting games by providing a training mode to practice what moves do what and to see all the blockbusters (AKA supers) that each character has, and veterans to fighting games by practicing combos, speaking of which the combo system is INSANE, by providing the ability to go over 100 hit combos, but back to the practice mode, veteran can practice their hit marks by applying hit boxes, blocking only, etc., with the inclusion of a menu saying how much damage a certain move does, how long said move stuns the player, how much health the player has, all that good stuff.2. Characters: Each character in the game has their own story mode and can be playable in arcade mode. The game has 8 characters which is very little for a fighting game, but the game is getting DLC characters with their own story mode, one of which has already been fully released (AKA Squigly). Each character has their own attributes, Peacock is a projectile type character, Cerebella does more damage but slower than some others, Double has the ability to morph into other characters and yeah.3. Story: Story is simple, there is a heart called the Skullheart that can grant any girl a wish, but one that has a impure soul turns into a rage maniac called the Skullgirl, which one has been turned into one, it's up to one of the 8 (9 if you include the DLC character) to get to the Skullgirl and Skullheart4. Music: If you’re a fan of jazzy tunes, then the music is up your alley. The music is composed by Michiru Yamane, the same person that did the Castlevania: Symphony of the Night soundtrack, so if you’re a fan of that, you might be a fan of this.5. Art: If you are an artist then you will love this. Each character frames is singly animated, which means roughed drawn, polished, and then colored. The art of the game is supposed to resemble a ""Dark Deco"" style art.6. Multiplayer: The multiplayer has modes such as lobbies for the group that wants to fight each other or a quick match mode for those who wants as it says, a quick match.Final Thoughts: This game is a great starter for anyone who wants to get into fighting games and it also appeals to veterans by adding a really good combo system. The only downside of the game is the lack of characters which I hope Lab Zero will add more, and they will because it says so in the feature DLC section in the game description. All and all, it’s a good game that you should pick up and have a go."
