76561198042015920,Recommended,245170,18851689,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,sensualtouching,"First off, I dont like fighting games. I can never seem to get into the gameplay and I am terrible at pulling off combos and moves in the most basic of forms, and as soon as you introduce a bit of difficulty Its GG. I love this game. It has a fluid yet simple combat/moveset that creates an interesting moveset for each character with the inputs being universal for simple moves. No ability feels extremly confusing and allows a novice to fighting games to be able to pick it up rather quickly and enjoy the game without having to spend hours trying to get the gameplay down. A great introductory fighting game. On the negative side the plot for each character feels bland as can be with each segment of diologue acting as a segway to the next fighter rather than plot development. Limited standard picks without having DLC (though some are free from time to time) but compared to other fighting games a lackluster roster. Overall the cons do not weight down the fun to be had for the low price that it demands. would definitly reccomend."
