,Recommended,245170,16288466,"Posted: 10 June, 2015",all,yung crystal pepsi,"An amazing fighting game made by fans, for fans. Everything about this game screams style, and you can really tell that it was made with a lot of love. The fast and frenetic gameplay is mainly inspired by the Marvel Vs. Capcom series, but also features the free-ratio system from Capcom Vs. SNK, so the gameplay will always be balanced no matter how many characters are on your team. The cast might be small, but every character feels completely different from one another (plus any additional DLC characters will be available for free for a limited time following their release). If you've never played a fighting game before, Skullgirls also features a very in-depth tutorial that not only teaches you how to play the game, but also teaches you the fundamentals and lingo of fighting games as a whole. Top it all off with an gorgeous Art Deco aesthetic and a classy soundtrack composed by Castlevania legend Michiru Yamane, and you have one of the best fighters of all time."
