,Recommended,245170,16156967,"Posted: 3 June, 2015",all,Mister Artorias,"Being sort of a rookie in the fighting genre, I think Skullgirls is a perfect way to really get used to otherwise hard-to-pull-off fighting combos in most fighting games I play. The controls are fantastic ( Preferably the controller ) and very responsive. The netcode ( Online play ) is surprisingly good compared to most PC fighting games. The animations are all hand-drawn, fluid, cartoony, and top notch. The character roster isn't massive, but big enough to have lots of variation between them; Not to mention each individual character has their own mini-storyline for you to complete. The game feels quite easy to get into,  you can even pull off a killer combo sometimes by just mashing buttons and that's not a bad thing. It shows that even beginners in the fighting genre can get into the game while still having difficult mechanics for veteran players to play around with.[TL;DR] - Skullgirls is a fun, easy-to-learn, visually impressive fighting game with an excellent online netcode that is definitely worth the price."
