,Recommended,245170,16784529,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,Halaa,"This has quickly become one of my favourite fighting games. Unlike other games in the genre, this one is fairly easy to get into. One of the reasons for this is because it actually has a really good tutorial that introduces some of the concepts of fighting games and some that are unique to this game alone, like infinite breakers. The game is very combo heavy but doesn't rely on near endless combos like you would see in a game like Marvel VS Capcom 3. This is because if a combo becomes too repetitive or too long, the other player has a chance to break out. However, clever players will intentionally drop their combos unexpectedly so that they can reset and keep going.The cast of characters is small, but each character feels very unique. You have rushdown characters like Filia and Ms. Fortune who apply pressure at all times, campy characters like Peacock who are very good at being an annoyance, powerhouses like Big Band who are slow but do tremendous amounts of damage, and grapple based characters like Beowulf and Cerebella who will grab you constantly. My personal favourite character is Squigly who is very good at zoning and creating long combos.Overall, I think this game is great for fighting game veterans and people who want to get into fighting games. I bought it on sale for around C$3.50 and all the DLC for about another C$4.00 and do not regret my purchase. Next time you see this on sale, consider buying it and maybe join me in a fight sometime."
