,Recommended,245170,18271879,"Posted: 30 September, 2015",all,Wanton,"This is an excellent game, and I'll give it my recommendation on its multiplayer and mechanics alone. However, if you are interested in single player, and you aren't a savant at fighting games, don't bother. The single player is compitently designed, if not a little easy right up until the end. I was able to beat every enemy on nightmare difficulty, only having to try again once, and I'm fairly new to fighting games. The final boss, Marie, has to be the single worst designed enemy I've encountered in any game. My philosophy on bosses is that they shouldn't be easily beaten, overly designed setpieces, but rather a do or die test of your skills at the game. Marie goes way too far in the opposite direction. She uses fluries of essentially unblockable projectile attacks, shadow attacks, and skeleton mines that will more often than not spawn under your character. Each of these things can knock a quarter of your health off in the easiest game mode. So for a fighter about countering and chaining together intricate combinations, to make the final test a 3 stage bullet hell where everything you've learned to that point is useless, and the only feasable way to win is to spam heavy attacks and pray you don't take a hit, seems like an almost unforgivable mistep."
