76561198141303718,Recommended,245170,16250781,"Posted: 7 June, 2015",all,Urzael,"Skullgirls, is a very fun game. I had played it for hours, without even trying the demo for it, I had bought it. It was one thing I had bought much recently. -- And all the games I had bought recently, this is one of my favorite so far. I had immense fun playing all the characters. My few favorites at the moment being Beowulf, Painwheel, and Miss Fortune. I give this game an 9.5/10, with the Red Sun seal of awesomeness. It is highly reccomended to have if your steam library, it is a fast pace fighter game, and deals out some rather interesting characters, the score ( Music ) Of the game is epic.Though it was repetative at times, it was rather badass, my favorite OST being Marie's, the final boss's theme. It had me feeling like I was fighting a scary necromancer, and that I was the one to take it down. There are some problems with this game, such as the controls being hard to get around, most fighting games have their light attacks mapped to A, B, X, Y on the controller. Though this game's attacks are mapped to RT, RB, LT, LB; making it a hard time to get used to the combat.Another problem I had encountered is that the normal difficulty is actually HARD. (Shocker! I know right?) No, it was actually difficult. The final boss, being broken in her defensive systems. The other enemies you had fought a long the way being easier to take down, to progress through the rather (Short) stories.Though I do see why you shortened the stories, you want people to get to the action, not care much about the story. (Most fighting games use this cliché) It had a rather bland level layout. Though the layout brought back nostalgia, as I remembered how the olden fighting games were, with bystanders watching the fight.A third and final problem I had found in the whole game, is that most of the characters are over powered, and broken when used by the A.I. As stated above, Marie is a hell of a boss, with an insane amount of defense, and offensive power. The other two characters who are broken, are Big Band; he is massive, deals out a lot of damage, and is faster than most characters. It was very upsetting to fight him, and I rage quit his fight multiple times. The other two who are annoyingly over powered are Beowulf, he can spam his attacks and land massive combos. As well as Peacock, the bomb throwing girl; she'll stand at one side of the map and will not let you move, or get anywhere close to her. She was a boring fight; and I sometimes refused to fight her.Though there were more good than bad in this game..Pros:Fun charactersMemorable charactersGreate soundtrack, (To those who enjoy music without any lyrics in it.)Nostalgic level designsCharacters can have color changes, and such.First 2-D I had enjoyedWell written storiesStories tie up, and show what would happen after each person killed the ""Skullgirl.""Cons:Broken charactersNormal difficulty, is challenging.Can get repetativeSexual content. (Panties, and bras, one girl's shirt falls off on one side. Large breasts on the nurse character, they are literally popping out of her shirt.)Tying up loose ends:This game is reccomended, it deserves to be in anyone's steam library. I will be playing more of this game; it was the most enjoyable time I have ever had in a fighting game, in my opinion it is more fun than Mortal Kombat. This game will always be played by me, and when I get the money I plan on buying all of the DLC. So the company who made this, continue what you're doing. Continue making these games, and push out more products! -- Stay Awesome -- RED SUN."
