76561198058282432,Recommended,245170,15481561,"Posted: 21 April, 2015",all,Rose,"I don't like fighting games. Really, I don't. I can't wrap my head around the idea that you need to push seven different keys at once to get a certain move to go off, and even when I do manage to finally get it down, there's no chance in hell that I'll be able to do it in the heat of a match. Besides, the idea of characters just fighting each other with very little reason always struck me as... shallow? That's the nicest word I have for it. Violence for no good reason isn't escapism, it's just people being awful to each other. Fighting games are, in my opinion, one of those things that I really would rather not have anything to do with.So, when I tell you that Skullgirls is perhaps my second or third favorite game of all times, you probably want to listen in.I don't know what it is about this insane, awesome romp of flashing lights and partly clothed girls that makes it such an experience for me, but it really is. The gameplay is the most fun I've had in a long, long time doing anything at all. The A.I. is engaging on it's own, and varried enough that it's not trivial to find easy exploits in it. Multiplayer support is actually surprisingly robust, and quite the enjoyable experience if you don't mind losing a lot. The characters are funny and dark and fully realized, even if the story is nothing to praise. The animations are beautiful, matching aesthetics and graphics in a way that is simply fun to look at. The soundtrack is nearly perfect, setting the tone brilliantly for each scene, managing to match the visuals in a highly appealing and completely competent way. The controls are easy enough to use that you can pick them up and start winning on the lower difficulty levels in only a half hour, but deep enough that you can continue to challenge yourself with more and more complex combinations. And, take it from me, you don't have to be very good to get a great experience from this game – I'm one of the worst gamers I know, and I still have an absolute blast.Oh, and the character models are hot. If your into that sort of thing. I guess I don't really consider that a big part of the experience, but it is technically true.If you don't mind playing an awesome and beautiful game, you should totally pick up Skullgirls. It won't disappoint you, I can guarantee it."
