76561198087446247,Recommended,245170,12711335,"Posted: 31 October, 2014",all,TTwizzle64,"As an animation enthusiast and active gamer, I was excited to find this game in development, back when it was only on Xbox 360 and Playstation 3. My favorite part was that nearly everything in this game, from the background to the character animations themselves, was hand-drawn. I respect any group of animators who put themselves through hand-drawn animation. Anyways, Skullgirls is a 2D fighting game about various girls with wacked-out themes fighting over an artifact dubbed ""the Skull Heart,"" giving the winner absolute power and near-immortality. But, who cares about the prize? Fighting games have rarely given good endings.Skullgirls features a very oddball cast of fighters. There's a schoolgirl with a hairy parasite, a circus freak who loves her pro wrestling, an adolscent girl who loves her cartoons, a literal cat burglar, a general who fights with her umbrella, a sexy ninja nurse, a demonic nun, a cybernetic cop that loves his jazz, a zombie girl with an undead dragon serpent, and, coming soon, an Egyptian goddess. A veru colorful cast, indeed.This game is great for tournament players and I'm glad the love for this game has increased tenfold. Casual gamers may want to stay away from multiplayer and online functions, but I recommend this game for being visually dynamic and beautiful while maintaining the fast-paced style of old-school fighting games."
