,Recommended,245170,18244574,"Posted: 28 September, 2015",all,SubrosianChainsawMassacre_|BC|,"You'll laugh, you'll cry, you'll wonder how the ♥♥♥♥ the♥♥♥♥♥♥on half of these girls don't just fall right out of their tops (I'm looking at you Cerebella).Skullgirls is a fighting game when you take control of 8 girls (along with another 4 and 2 guys as DLC characters) who beat the ever-loving chocolate syrup out of each other in order to acquire/destroy/wish on an artifact called the Skull Heart. Or if you don't care about story mode (because you're not really playing this game for a story anyway), you can just play arcade mode instead and deal with your typical fighting game flair in that department.In terms of actual gameplay, it's just what you'd expect from a fighting game. There are six attack buttons, the usual punch and kick buttons along with silky smooth control and overly flashy special moves that are just as entertaining as they are damaging (which is a lot, by the way). All of the characters have vastly different fighting styles (with the exception of Fukua, but there's a reason for it), and there's an anti-infinite system in place to keep infinites from happening...in theory anyway.The anti-infinite system is a fantastic idea, I can't even begin to count the sheer number of times I ended up stuck against a wall in almost every tournament fighter I've ever played. The problem is that, to put it simply...it doesn't work.The system only registers certain kinds of combos as infinites, and the system is so damn easy to exploit and sidestep that it's borderline pointless. Now, this is only a real problem online, where everyone can do itexceptyou, and the game doesn't match you based on MMR or anything, you just get pitted against a random person who is more likely than not far better than you.However, other than the worthless anti-infinite system and rage enducing online play, this game is fantastic. I just recommend playing it with a controller. I have a USB SNES controller which works perfectly, but you're probably going to be using an Xbox or PS3/PS4 controller.So, what are you waiting for? Get this titilating fighter right now, or wait till a sale, your decision. Just remember not to play it when your parents are around."
