,Recommended,245170,16178869,"Posted: 3 June, 2015",all,kosmani,"This is a wonderful fighting game that I want to recommend to anyone even remotely interested in the genre. With an expansive (optional) tutorial mode that explains basic mechanics very well, a great roster/gameplay, and a wonderful dev team, it's a must-have in the fighting genre.The art style and animations are done very well, and the backgrounds and stages are all very pretty to look at while you beat your opponent to a pulp. On top of that, some of the game mechanics are truly innovative; you can string 100+ hit combos if you practice hard enough because of the organic and fluid combo system that let's you string essentially any move with another, but if you reach any 'infinite' territory, repeated moves can be punished with a block breaker. The characters are also all unique and interesting, enough that you'll want to try to learn how to play much more than just one of them.Overall, it's a fast-paced game and I can't help but hope that many more people buy it, since it is definitely worth much more than the 3$ asking price. Especially since all future DLC is free for the first 3 months after its release. Beowulf is free right now, and so will the next few characters."
