,Recommended,245170,13667046,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,Party Yeen,"In a world dominated by polygonal button-mashing fighters from Japanese companies, it is incredibly refreshing to see games like Skullgirls. With skilled gameplay that feels like classic Capcom/SNK fighting games and features beautifully hand-drawn characters. Every fighter is enjoyable to play and has a compelling story mode. There are tag team battles, complex combo systems, assists, and even a very robust tutorial mode that will teach you all you need to know to play competitively whether you're a newbie or a seasoned fighting game veteran.Skullgirls also has a rather rare distinction among fighting games as a whole in that the cast of playable characters are almost all women (and unlike Dead or Alive it's not just for eye candy). So if you're looking for a high quality fighting game that shows that there is definite progression in the gaming world (or you just want to play a really fun fighting game) I would definitely recommend this one."
