76561197972351873,Recommended,245170,8350568,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,DanTheTimid,"Let me state up front, this game is brilliant on so many levels, one of the best fighting games not just of this era, but of all time.  That said, there are five issues this game has that any would be buyer needs to know up front.1) The community is pretty awful.  Exceptionally so if you're a casual player.  Don't get me wrong, there are some good people in it too, but its not uncommon for people to treat you poorly in game, and even more common for them to treat you poorly on forums... and then instead of other people in the community chastining the poor behavior, they will actually LIKE the hateful or bully post directed at your person.  I'm talking posts where they verbally abuse you, curse at you, and tell you to quit the game.  These terrible people have likely lead to the community remaining small, so you need to have thick skin, especially if you just want to enjoy the game as a game and not a second job.2) The art, while beautiful beyond words and easily as good as if not superior to any other fighting game on the market, is very fan service heavy, with a largely female cast, many of which wear the sort of clothes you'd expect to see in a strip club, over bodies that could almost go toe to toe with Dragon's Crown.  Frankly, all that doesn't bother me, but it does bother some people so it bares mentioning.3) This is a combo fighter.  If you like combo fighters, great, personally I hate combo fighters.  Yet everything else about this game is so good that I can look past the combos and enjoy the game.  Some people can't.  Its worth noting that unlike some combo fighters, the combos in this game are VERY beginner friendly, most characters having at least one solid combo that can be done by average human beings with out spending months in training, but as a combo fighter this still means that a good portion of every match consists of one player playing solitaire.  Also, being a combo fighter means this game has a pretty large gap between beginners and intermediates, which wouldn't be that big a deal if not for the next issue.4) The game has no skill based match making.  The game once had skill based match making, but my understanding is it was removed because the community was so small that finding matches took forever.  In my opinion this decision only made a bad situation worse as beginners are routinely matched with experts and usually no fun is had by either player in those situations.  It should be noted that the game does have a good lobby format and good netcode, so there are ways to have fun against players of your skill online, but its much more difficult to set up then it shoudl be.5)The roster is small.  This again, doesn't bother me, as the roster is also extremely varied and better balanced then many other fighters out there, so I'd argue that the number of viable options is actually on par with or actually higher then most other fighting games, but I know some people really want to see a huge screen of characters to choose from, even if half of them are useless or clones of the other half.So in conclusion, what's good?  The music!  The story!  The characters!  The graphics!  The gameplay!  The netcode!  The training mode!  The tutorials!  The frequent updates!  So if those 5 bad things didn't scare you off, you owe it to yourself to give this game a chance.  It's that good.  But I feel its vital a potential new player be aware of the issues the game has upfront, especially those with the community, or the community really will always remain small and dominated by the same intolerrant bullies it is currently."
