76561197993236928,Recommended,245170,13000958,"Posted: 18 November, 2014",all,DemonScuzz,"Coming from a brand new player: Skullgirls is a fantastic fighting game. It is not, however, a particularly FRIENDLY fighting game. The tutorials are incredibly detailed and can easily overwhelm you, demanding mastery of precise controls when all you want to do is just punch the other character until they fall down. Don't let it intimidate you, though, there's a terrific game just waiting for you to catch up to it.My advice to fellow beginners: select ""Single Player Mode"", set the difficulty to ""Sleepwalk"" (the easiest possible), and go nuts. Story or Arcade, just grab a girl and dive in headfirst. Then swap to another. And another. See who you like and who you don't. Then start studying the move lists, poking through the tutorials, and digging into the details. If you're like me, this first taste of actual (though super easy mode) gameplay won't make you an expert, but it will make you hungry for more."
