76561198021471207,Recommended,245170,12991814,"Posted: 18 November, 2014",all,Xx_Avenger_xX,"New to fighting games? You could go play Street Fighter IV and get thrown in the deep end with just a list of character chains to perform, but you won't learn anything that way.You wont know anything about Mix-ups, hit confirmation, overheads, cross ups and how to block them. This is why I recommend anyone new to fighting games to play Skullgirls. It actually teaches you important game mechanics with an excellent tutorial, which is something Street Fighter IV fails at completely.The game is heavily influenced by Marvel vs Capcom 2 from what I can tell .. because I played that game to death back in the early 2000s ... it plays exactly the same, with team assists, snapback attacks, ground recovery, super jumps, air dashes and hyper combos ... errr I mean Blockbuster Attacks .. :)Combos are clean and feel great to perform and its not hard to rack up hits with just some basic chains.The art style is great and the music and sounds are very fitting. Character art is very ""anime"", while it might not appeal to some I like it a lot.Highly recommended."
,Recommended,245170,12992514,"Posted: 18 November, 2014",all,Trance_85,"This game is definitely one of the most hard-core fighting games I've ever come across; supremely high skill ceiling.AMAZING netcode: I played someone from Japan with over 300 ping and it felt better than playing someone in europe on Ultra Street Fighter 4.The fact that it was on sale on steam has also boosted the size of the playerbase and hopefully we'll all stay :D. Now to somehow convince everyone playing Street Fighter to come to Skullgirls...Pro Tip: If you're using Keyboard to play this game try this layout (AKA Hitbox Layout - Google ""how to hitbox for tips on using this layout - SOCD doesn't work on keyboards):A=Left, S=Down, D=Right, Space=Up/Jump - this makes doing 360 grabs a lot easier; I like to hit space with my right thumb+LK+LP if that helps ^_^.IOP for LP, MP, HPJKL for LK, MK, HKFor assists and Macro's you can use whatever - I use '[' and ';'Just be warned that you MUST use a keyboard that has some sort of Anti-Ghosting and more than 6-Key Roll Over (google this if you're not sure what it means) or a lot of your inputs won't even come out."
