76561198254326902,Recommended,245170,20732128,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,zankurous,"Be mindful that this review focuses on the offline experience, having said that, on with the review!Looking for a gorgeous looking fighting game filled with intriguing characters and made by people who obviously love the fighting game genre? Skullgirls may be just what your looking for.Pros:+ Gorgeous graphics featuring a hillarious cartoon-like style.+ Intriguing storyline.+ An unusual cast filled with a fun yet varied moveset and different strategies to use. (No two characters play the same!)+ Face your oponnents either by using a single character or a two or three member team!+ Fast paced gameplay that reward the use of variety in combos (Apparently without infinites to worry about...)+ Very responsive controls (either a joystick or a gamepad will do just fine!)+ Comprehensive tutorials will get you up to speed not only to this game, but on fighting games in general.+ Great soundtrack and professional voicework filled with plenty of charm.+ Plenty of in-game nods and references to videogames & media in general for you to find.+ Runs great on the average pc. (No need for a dedicated gaming pc for this one!)Cons:- The gameplay style favors players with agressive playstyles, so beginners may feel overwhelmed at first.- The average combo count borders on the excessive and a little mistake can cost you dearly.- The story mode was apparently designed with an arcade game mindset (In other words, it is very short!)- Could use more single player modes (either a survival or a mission mode would do wonders!)- Most of the references in the game are definitely geared toward older fighting game players only.- It may be a staple of the genre, but the final boss (the skullgirl) is hillariously cheap! ;)In short, I definitely love this game and look forward to either a sequel or more content! Be sure to grab it if you are a seasoned fighting game veteran or a beginner with a interest in the genre!"
