76561198138936799,Recommended,245170,30850611,Posted: 31 March,all,djumbreon,"Hands down one of the best fighting games you will ever play.Skullgirls is what you get when you take a team of passionate developers and a dedicated fan base, then mash them together.The gameplay is a two 2D fighter, with a play style thats somewhere between the line of street fighter meets marvel vs capcom, fortunately, so long as your willing to take some time and practice, even if its just one character, you can stand your own ground in competetive online multiplayer. Skullgirls roster is a little on the small side with only 8 playable characters ( not counting the 6 DLC fighters), but good thing to note when it comes to fighting games with small rosters is that the options may not be all over the place, but at least you know that balancing is being taken seriously.Online are pretty straight forward, you play best out of three, then rejoin a lobby unless your in your own private lobby or in a tourney. online is stable given the kind of game skullgirls is. for an indie game, while its never really frequnt, you will run into players online in most instances you play. however there will be days when you find yourself waiting endleslly for a quick match opponent and nothing will happen.Learning how to play, even if your someone who doesn't ever play fighting games, the tutorial in skullgirls is amazingly well done. its got itself defined to the very last detail on combos and game macanics that you'll be able to master so long as you take some time to practice. I myself am yet to finish the tutorial by the time this goes up. simply put, its alot more advanced then pushing one or two buttons, you'll be coming back to it every so often to try learning something else about the game. Further more, some of the things the game teaches the player are even universal tips on just playing traditional fighting games in general.The story to this game is weighed heavily on which character you choose for the story mode, and every character has a path that differs greatly among everyone. while there are many details left unmentioned and while somethings may need to be pieced together, its beyond worth the time to try out with everyone at least once. There's so much there, along with so much of it being left open to the point you would be like me and ask yourself ""there's a comic series for this...right?""Things such as the soundtrack, artsyle, and even the play style of skullgirls aew juat enjoyable themselves and make it feel like for just 10 dollars, your definetly gettin your money's worth with this one.10/10"
