,Recommended,245170,2027598,"Posted: 29 September, 2013",all,Punymeyer,"This game is pretty amazing.  I can't think of a single gripe that I have with Skullgirls.  The netcode, graphics, music, sounds, characters, theme...it's all so good.  The gameplay is solid, but I personally prefer fighters that are less combo-heavy and more grounded.  That's just a preference and something other people should consider, but even if you don't intend to make this game your main fighter you should still pick it if you're a fan of the genre, even if you just mess around in training mode and single player because it really does have a lot of character.The story mode is charming enough to warrant a play through with each character too.  I think the ""2nd Encore"" DLC includes voice acting for the story as well, so that would probably be worth getting.  I own that DLC but haven't tried it out yet.The studio that made it is brilliant, and certain bigger studios should be taking a look at them for inspiration.  And if you're on the fence because of the price of the game + all the DLC, then know that it goes on sale quite often and even gets included in bundles from time to time."
