,Recommended,245170,32211784,Posted: 5 June,all,Kawaii Anime Grill #TrapsAintGay,"My actual playtime is much higher, as the game comes with a free beta and I have well over 80 hours on that.Skullgirls is a stylish, mechanically deep and complex fighting game. Don't let the art style or the attractive leading ladies for you, this is a game that has a very high skill ceiling and plays a lot like Marvel versus Capcom and Street Fighter. The main draw of this game is admittedly it's beautiful art style, it looks like it came straight out of the 60s cartoon and a lot of the characters sign and that is great,  they took full advantage of this cartoon is art style and design of the characters and each character is very unique not only in the design but their move set, miss fortune   will use her head as a drill, Valentine will beat in you to death with a lollipop-it's all very surreal and adds to the fun of the game. Even with the over-the-top and bombastic art style however, this game is not one that is completely values style over substance it isn't as deep as some other fighting games on the market it does have a few issues where combos can go on and be unbelievably Easley reset, however many of those issues have been fixed since I've stopped playing as the game is still pants for balance every few months. Furthermore, I strongly recommend this game to anyone who is new to the fighting games genre as the controls are unbelievably tight and simple enough for someone who is new to the genre to grasp and is complex enough for veterans to have something to sink their teeth into. Overall this is a game definitely worth buying food for us, I cannot recommend this game enough."
