,Recommended,245170,13919480,"Posted: 9 January, 2015",all,McDuders,"EDIT: After playing over 200 hours of this game on record, I've decided to redo my review of this game to make it easier to read.Here's what you need to know:Prices:-Standard game: $10. Characters and color swaps: $2 ea (5 to choose from. Buying the $2 color swaps is every color for life). 2nd Encore (all dlc, rebalanced game AND MORE): $15. Full game for life (2nd Encore and the standard game): $25. Does not include regional equivelant or sales.The positives:+6 button fighter, 2D, 8 directions, most similar to Marvel vs. Capcom.+Fairly cheap for what you get in a fighting game, even without sales.+EXCELLENT tutorial for beginners!+ANY controller will work, and easy input configuration!+Keyboard is not only possible, BUT ENCOURAGED!+HUGE SELECTION OF SEXY WAIFUS FOR THE PICKING (mine is Big Band)+14 characters, each with completely different traits and playstyles! (9 included without DLC characters)+Play a selection of 1, 2, or 3 characters in tag-team or solo matches! CUSTOM ASSISTS!+The smoothest online around, utilizing GGPO!+Fantastic anime-inspired art in a unique ""dark-deco"" film style!+Amazing music!+MODS ARE AVAILABLE!+Awesome community! (come see us at Discord sometime!)+Russian and drunk English announcer! English and Japanese voices for every character! Joke voices for select characters! DRUNK JAPENESE ANNOUNCER!!!The negatives:-*gasp* NOT ALL THE CHARACTERS ARE FEMALES! Big Band and Beowulf are the only playable males by popular demand.-Hard-to-navigate menu at first (default controls for keyboard: wasd, j confirm and k cancel)-Story mode is nothing that special (general ""what-if"" scenarios for each character). DLC stories are pretty good though!-Combos are essential to learning the end-game, making the learning curve VERY STEEP for beginners.-Online quick matches and lobbies are TOUGH. Expect for tears to flow and salt to shimmer.-No longer updated by Lab Zero (they have moved on to Indivisible and other games)Expert review coming soon, but expect the game to be a balanced Marvel vs. Capcom 2 with much more to offer in terms of mechanics."
