76561198202632283,Recommended,245170,33917294,Posted: 30 July,all,P1ka the Melee Lord,"As a professional Melee player, I've always been a fan of fast-paced fighting games, so when I saw this game in EVO, I was immediately drawn to it. When I first started playing the game, I had high hopes, and Skullgirls passed every expectancy easily. This game is a great fighter that can appeal to beginners and advanced players alike as there is an in-game tutorial with many different tips. One of my favorite things of the game is how it focuses on long combos. As a Marth main in Melee, I am used to chaining big combos and making sure the opponent doesn't have a chance to retaliate, and this game has characters who can do just that, like Parasoul who has multiple attacks that can keep the opponent airborne. Another highlight of this game is its hitboxes. This game has very precise hitboxes for each character, barely going over the sprites of the characters, unlike games like Smash 4 which has bigger hitboxes than normal. Overall, this game is a great fighter and a must-buy for Melee fans."
