ns or settings are fine not much to talk about. I also like that it gives you a tutorial on the mechanics of the game and how 2-D fighters are played which really surpizes me and alot helps me understand the game even more.Then we have the bad onesThe Story:The story sucks when you try putting it together and there is this gap giving you evidence about the world of skullgirls. What even suck is that you have alot of great minor characters that can be expressed even more instead of making them into a flat character. It has that twisted metal type endings which can leave you satisfied or feel strange. I like to mention about the cut endings that the player can chose and some of it seems better.The Recognition:Skullgirls has like a hidden gem type feel. Like its not that well knowned since we got some main stream games out there especialy in the fighting genres. Yeah i mean like there was a fundraiser but like once it stop thats when you know the hype is gone. Also the fact that theres not much other players using the online multiplayer so its hard to come by a guy/girl playing this game.Overall:I give it a 3.5/5, its a good game worth playing and its fun to play with friends and also like the character there. Its really a worth to buy it and its good for starters who are new to the 2-D fighing aspects but in play style use a joystick or a controller. Its good but i dislike the storytelling and the characters (not the fighters).Please note that these are my thoughts about the game and if you hated it or disagree with feel free to comment about out because i like to hear your thoughts about it as well. I respect others thoughts because its there point of view of seeing this review and game. Thank you for having the time to read this and learning a reviews thoughts about the game, have fun."
