76561198258072835,Recommended,245170,34378624,Posted: 20 August,all,FreezyCastform99 | gamekit.com,"Soooooooooo..... where do I even start? I bought Skullgirls because I saw it in a few Videos from YouTubers like Joshscorcher and thought it looked interesting. I first played this game with a keyboard because I didn´t have a gamepad, and although it was playable, it wasn´t all too much fun. Then, a year or two later, I got one and replayed it after I got the 2nd Encore Upgrade. I think I can now safely say that Skullgirls is, without a doubt, the best fighting game I played to this day. Controlls are responsive, gameplay is fluent and balanced out nicely, Characters, while limited, are all unique enough in their playstiles and mechanics to make up for the limited roster. Online is where this game shines the best when compared to other fighting games. I played Street Fighter 4 and 5, Smash Bros Brawl and WiiU/3DS, UMvC3, Rivals of Aether and many others, but none comes even close to Skullgirls when it comes to stable netplay. If only more players would be online, it would be just perfect. And most impressive of all, the story is amazing. Weird, right? A fighting Game with a good story isn´t really something you see so often...Pros+Great, responsive controlls+Amazinig Characters with interesting and unique Stories and playstyles+Well composed soundtrack+Amazingly stable Online play+Detailed and Informative Tutorials for both general Gameplay and indivdual characters+A lot of cultural and nerdy refernces hidden in character colors and quotesCons-Limited Roster (although not a con for me, for some it can be one)-Online mode is empty most of the timeAll in all, Skullgirls gives you fluid and fast gameplay with a unique cast of characters and what I think to be the best netplay in any fighting game ever for 10 bucks. If you want the full and best experience, get the 2nd Encore Upgrade. Other than that, I recommend this game to anyone who is a pro, a casual or someone who wants to learn fighting games, and seeing how this is one of the first fighters I´ve ever played seriously, I think that´s not so much of a stretch to say. Gamepads, although optional, are more than recommended for the full experience"
