76561198045186609,Recommended,245170,34164345,Posted: 11 August,all,Vainy_DeLigh,"I bought this game in like 2013 and just let it sit in my steam library. I primarily play Melee and wanted to get into another fighter at the time but never really gave it a chance past the purchase. Tried getting into Street Fighter 4 Ultra at the time but the depths and mechanics of the game didn't really click with me. I guess it was just my fault for never trying MVC but this game gelled with me as soon as i started playing it.A friend and I started playing a month ago and it has grasped me since. The mechanics and depth of the game is ridiculous. The IPS and undizzy prevents loops and makes you be creative with your combos. This game just oozes creativity too, whilst being obviously inspired by many old fighters, most notably MVC2. The assist system is dope, allowing you to input whatever move you want as an assist. The character cast is pretty small but honestly all the characters are sick. It's balanced really well and each character has their own tools that let them work in whatever matchup.I don't really know what else to say, it's 2017 and I just started playing this game, not because theres really a big scene for it, just because it's an amazing game. I hope if anyone sees this review they try it out, it's alot of fun. Oh, I guess I should say if you've never played mvc or anything similiar to this you're going to be getting stomped unless you learn the systems. That might be a turnoff but if you find you like the game the journey to learning each mechanic and your character is worth it."
